\f5\b  Key Results\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Under strict privacy constraints ($\\epsilon = 2.0$), the classical model exhibits high variance and instability. In contrast, 
\f5\b HALO
\f0\b0  maintains deterministic convergence. Both models respect the privacy threshold, but the quantum approach retains a significantly higher utility curve.\
